fr.zelus.jarvis.plugins.slack.module

Class SlackModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.zelus.jarvis.core.JarvisModule
      • fr.zelus.jarvis.plugins.slack.module.SlackModule

  • public class SlackModule
extends JarvisModule
    A JarvisModule class that connect and interacts with the Slack API.

    This module manages a connection to the Slack API, and provides a set of JarvisActions to interact with the Slack API:

    • Reply: reply to a user input
    • PostMessage: post a message to a given Slack channel

    This class is part of jarvis' core modules, and can be used in an orchestration model by importing the core.SlackModule package.

    • Constructor Detail

      • SlackModule

        public SlackModule(JarvisCore jarvisCore,
                   Configuration configuration)
        Constructs a new SlackModule from the provided JarvisCore and Configuration.

        This constructor initializes the underlying Slack client with the Slack bot API token retrieved from the Configuration.

        Note: SlackModule requires a valid Slack bot API token to be initialized, and calling the default constructor will throw an IllegalArgumentException when looking for the Slack bot API token.

        Parameters:
        jarvisCore - the JarvisCore instance associated to this module
        configuration - the Configuration used to retrieve the Slack bot API token
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided jarvisCore or configuration is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided Slack bot API token is null or empty
